   82|       |  // set if the thread tries to use AVX512 anyway.  Thus, to safely and
   83|       |  // consistently use AVX512 on macOS we'd need to check the kernel version as
   84|       |  // well as detect AVX512 support using a macOS-specific method.  We don't
   85|       |  // bother with this, especially given Apple's transition to arm64.
   86|       |  return false;
